com.nymi.api

Class NymiAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nymi.api.NymiAdapter

  • public class NymiAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
    The starting point for all operations involving NymiDevice objects.

    The NymiAdapter is the starting point for all operations involving NymiDevice objects. It persist all provisions it creates in app-local storage. All provisioned NymiDevice are exposed via getDevices().

    The NymiAdapter needs access to your application's context to access bluetooth and thus must get initialized at each run of your application.

    As discussed in the package overview, NEAs may only communicate with Nymi Bands with which they share a provision. The provisioning is initiated by the user; If instructed by the NEA to startProvision(com.nymi.api.NymiAdapter.NymiProvisionCallback), NymiAdapter will continuously scan for provisioning bands and initiate the provisioning process. The provisioning process involves an agreement step wherein the band displays a fixed LED pattern, known as an agreement pattern, also known to the NEA. This agreement step gives the opportunity for the application to confirm with the the user that the application is about to provision with the intended device (and this confirmation is strongly recommended for all applications). If the user confirms the application has found the intended peer, the application may requests the provisioning process be completed via setPattern(java.util.BitSet).

    NymiAdapter uses your device's bluetooth radio to interact with Nymi Bands and requires BLUETOOTH permission. BLUETOOTH_ADMIN is currently also required to start the bluetooth at NymiAdapter initialization; this behaviour may change in the future.

    The NymiAdapter can be configured to use the local network connection to talk to a nymulator rather than using the device's bluetooth and talking to physical bands. This mode is intended for development and not production. When operating in this mode, the INTERNET permission is required.

    The NymiAdapter is a singleton. Obtain the instance with getInstance(). Additionally, a NymiAdapter will either be able to use Bluetooth and talk to physical Nymi Bands or it will use the network to contact a nymulator, but not both. Which mode will be available to your application is determined at build time.

      • init

        public boolean init(Context context,
                    java.lang.String neaName,
                    NymiAdapter.NymiInitCallback callback)
        Initializes the NymiAdapter, including bluetooth, and recovers provisions from persistent storage.

        This must be called before your application can interact with the API. This initialization takes some time, and a callback is fired upon completion, enabling your application to start while this runs in the background. No other NymiAdapter methods are available while the initialization is in progress.

        Parameters:
        context - your application's context; needed to access bluetooth.
        neaName - the name of your application; this string will be associated with any provisions created by this NEA, and will be displayed to the user in the provision management section of the Nymi Companion Application If longer than 16 characters, only the first 16 will be used.
        callback - callback to deliver operation results.

      • finish

      • startProvision

        public boolean startProvision(NymiAdapter.NymiProvisionCallback callback)
        Configure and initiate provisioning with nearby bands.

        Provisioning a Nymi Band with a new NEA is a process initiated by the user, and so can only appear asynchronously to an NEA. This function tells the NymiAdapter to initiate the provisioning process with any such Nymi Band it discovers and determines the callback by which your NEA is notified of agreements.

        Parameters:
        callback - the callback to fire upon agreement.

      • setPattern

        public boolean setPattern(java.util.BitSet agreementPattern)
        Requests provisioning with Nymi Band displaying the provided pattern.

        If the provided pattern is not set on the band, no callback will fire.

        Parameters:
        agreementPattern - the pattern displaying on the intended provisioning peer
